listen, if science and medicine contradict the Bible,

00:44:54.899 --> 00:44:58.479
it's the Bible that's our authority, amen?

00:44:58.479 --> 00:44:59.939
But in this particular case,

00:44:59.939 --> 00:45:02.139
they support what the scriptures say.

00:45:03.279 --> 00:45:05.699
But I want you to look in Genesis chapter number nine.

00:45:05.699 --> 00:45:08.579
I want you to look at the example of Noah.

00:45:08.579 --> 00:45:10.719
Now, let me ask you this.

00:45:10.719 --> 00:45:15.719
Do you think Noah intended to get drunk

00:45:16.319 --> 00:45:18.739
and have this situation happen in his life?

00:45:19.759 --> 00:45:20.819
I would say no.

00:45:21.679 --> 00:45:23.359
If you look at the life of Noah

00:45:23.359 --> 00:45:24.859
and you look at all that's taking place,

00:45:24.859 --> 00:45:27.519
the Bible says of Noah in chapter number six

00:45:27.519 --> 00:45:29.559
that he found grace in the eyes of the Lord.

00:45:29.559 --> 00:45:30.399
Why?

00:45:30.399 --> 00:45:32.679
He was a just man, perfect in his generations,

00:45:32.679 --> 00:45:34.799
and Noah walked with God.

00:45:34.799 --> 00:45:37.279
As soon as they got off of the ark, what did he do?

00:45:37.279 --> 00:45:41.519
He offered sacrifices, built an altar, and made sacrifices.

00:45:41.519 --> 00:45:42.959
But in Genesis chapter number nine,

00:45:42.959 --> 00:45:45.519
the Bible says in verse number 20,

00:45:46.239 --> 00:45:48.679
and Noah began to be a husbandman and he planted a vineyard

00:45:48.679 --> 00:45:52.519
and he drank of the wine and was drunken

00:45:52.519 --> 00:45:54.419
and he was uncovered within his tent.

00:45:54.419 --> 00:45:55.959
And Ham, the father of Canaan,

00:45:55.959 --> 00:45:57.359
saw the nakedness of his father

00:45:57.359 --> 00:45:59.119
and told his two brethren without.

00:45:59.119 --> 00:46:01.159
Shem and Jephath come and they took a garment

00:46:01.159 --> 00:46:02.439
and laid it upon both their shoulders,

00:46:02.439 --> 00:46:04.719
went backward, covered the nakedness of their father,

00:46:04.719 --> 00:46:05.959
and their faces were backward

00:46:05.959 --> 00:46:07.419
and they saw not his father's nakedness.

00:46:07.419 --> 00:46:08.599
Noah awoke from his wine

00:46:08.599 --> 00:46:10.919
and knew what his younger son had done unto him.

00:46:10.919 --> 00:46:13.379
He said this, cursed be Canaan, a servant of servants,

00:46:13.379 --> 00:46:14.879
shall he be unto his brethren.

00:46:16.059 --> 00:46:17.319
And I look at the text of Scripture,

00:46:17.319 --> 00:46:18.979
see the New Testament tells us this,

00:46:18.979 --> 00:46:21.859
that before the flood, they were eating and drinking

00:46:21.859 --> 00:46:23.459
and being merry and so on and so forth.

00:46:23.459 --> 00:46:27.419
And so obviously, people learned

00:46:27.419 --> 00:46:29.219
how to make the fruit of the vine

00:46:29.219 --> 00:46:32.279
into an alcoholic beverage prior to the flood,

00:46:32.279 --> 00:46:34.179
according to what we find in the New Testament,

00:46:34.179 --> 00:46:37.699
Matthew speaking about that time before the flood.

00:46:37.699 --> 00:46:39.339
Now, if we understand that

00:46:39.339 --> 00:46:40.799
and we look at this text of Scripture

00:46:40.799 --> 00:46:42.059
and we find that he was a husbandman

00:46:42.059 --> 00:46:42.899
and he planted a vineyard,

00:46:43.399 --> 00:46:45.299
he understood how to make the alcoholic beverage

00:46:45.299 --> 00:46:47.419
because the Bible says he was drunken.

00:46:47.419 --> 00:46:51.179
He didn't get drunk by just drinking the fruit of the vine.

00:46:51.179 --> 00:46:55.139
And the Scriptures say that he was uncovered within his tent.

00:46:55.139 --> 00:46:59.179
Do you really think that a man with the testimony of Noah

00:46:59.179 --> 00:47:02.699
in Genesis chapter number six, seven, eight,

00:47:02.699 --> 00:47:04.379
and into chapter number nine up to this point,

00:47:04.379 --> 00:47:09.059
do you think that he set out to drink that fruit of the,

00:47:09.059 --> 00:47:11.179
or to drink that wine that he made

00:47:12.059 --> 00:47:16.739
and to get drunk and to end up uncovered in his tent?

00:47:16.739 --> 00:47:21.459
To bring a curse upon the, you see in verse number 25,

00:47:21.459 --> 00:47:22.699
he said, a curse would be Canaan,

00:47:22.699 --> 00:47:24.939
a servant of a servant shall I be to his brethren.

00:47:24.939 --> 00:47:27.179
Do you think that's what he set out to do?

00:47:27.179 --> 00:47:28.859
I'd say no.

00:47:28.859 --> 00:47:31.819
And it takes me back to one of the quotes that I shared.

00:47:31.819 --> 00:47:35.099
One can never know if he will control it

00:47:35.099 --> 00:47:37.899
or if it will control him.

00:47:38.779 --> 00:47:41.979
And so as we look at the subject this evening

00:47:41.979 --> 00:47:44.819
and we not only look at the text of Scripture

00:47:44.819 --> 00:47:45.859
from the book of Proverbs,

00:47:45.859 --> 00:47:49.619
but answer the question that was posed over the summer,

00:47:51.379 --> 00:47:55.579
my answer for you is that as a believer

00:47:55.579 --> 00:47:57.139
of the Bible, of the Scriptures,

00:47:57.139 --> 00:48:00.019
as someone that wants to walk with God and please God,

00:48:00.019 --> 00:48:02.659
I believe that the answer in regard to alcohol and wine

00:48:02.659 --> 00:48:04.359
is total abstinence.

00:48:05.159 --> 00:48:07.919
Because it is an irrefutable fact

00:48:07.919 --> 00:48:10.039
that a man that does not drink at all

00:48:10.039 --> 00:48:11.679
will never get drunk one time

00:48:11.679 --> 00:48:14.879
and will certainly never become a drunk.

00:48:16.399 --> 00:48:18.559
I got a phone call several years ago

00:48:19.559 --> 00:48:21.839
from a relative of someone

00:48:21.839 --> 00:48:25.119
that was very concerned about their relative.

00:48:25.999 --> 00:48:28.279
And they asked me if I would go make a visit.

00:48:28.279 --> 00:48:30.359
It was a Saturday evening, it was late.

00:48:31.239 --> 00:48:35.399
I try to really keep my Saturday evenings free.

00:48:35.399 --> 00:48:39.119
Sunday, church, be prepared physically

00:48:39.119 --> 00:48:40.599
and mentally and emotionally.

00:48:40.599 --> 00:48:42.959
I like to get to bed early on Saturday evening.

00:48:44.479 --> 00:48:46.559
And so I went to make this visit

00:48:46.559 --> 00:48:51.199
and I found an individual that was drunk out of their mind.

00:48:53.279 --> 00:48:54.759
They were drunk on wine.

00:48:54.759 --> 00:48:57.359
They didn't drink any hard liquor.

00:48:57.359 --> 00:48:58.559
They were drunk on wine.

00:49:01.079 --> 00:49:04.440
And I could not understand as I was trying to,

00:49:04.440 --> 00:49:06.519
on the behalf of this other family member,

00:49:06.519 --> 00:49:08.000
help and minister.

00:49:09.579 --> 00:49:11.859
And after a extended period of time,

00:49:11.859 --> 00:49:13.879
I asked the individual, I said,

00:49:13.879 --> 00:49:15.399
so let me just ask you this,

00:49:15.399 --> 00:49:18.919
what made you drink?

00:49:18.919 --> 00:49:19.879
Like, why?

00:49:21.799 --> 00:49:23.599
And this is the answer, I promise you,

00:49:23.599 --> 00:49:24.679
this is the answer.

00:49:25.559 --> 00:49:27.119
The red skin's lost.

00:49:28.079 --> 00:49:30.000
And I was so disappointed

00:49:31.279 --> 00:49:33.519
and I just wanted to take one drink.

00:49:37.359 --> 00:49:39.719
And I'm drunk out of my mind.

00:49:39.719 --> 00:49:42.619
Within the next two and a half weeks,

00:49:43.559 --> 00:49:45.519
the individual had to be transported to the hospital

00:49:45.519 --> 00:49:47.299
on a number of occasions.

00:49:47.299 --> 00:49:50.579
The individual had threatened to take his own life.

00:49:51.599 --> 00:49:54.919
There were requirements to have safety checks

00:49:54.919 --> 00:49:57.919
by law enforcement to go check and do a welfare check.

00:49:59.279 --> 00:50:00.119
Because the man.

00:50:00.119 --> 00:50:05.719
was disappointed with a sporting event and the outcome of it and took one drink.

00:50:07.639 --> 00:50:13.479
He thought he was going to take one drink. And you say, but pastor, that never happened to me.

00:50:13.479 --> 00:50:20.599
Wine is a mocker. Strong drink is raging. Whosoever is deceived thereby is not wise.

00:50:21.479 --> 00:50:28.039
I think the most wise position is to say total abstinence. I've tried to do my best on giving

00:50:28.039 --> 00:50:35.559
the answer from the scriptures, not being partial to anything that I've just kind of come up with my

00:50:35.559 --> 00:50:41.719
own opinion, but the scriptures seem to be clear to me. And we have to take that position of total

00:50:41.719 --> 00:50:49.079
abstinence. I hope this evening it's been a help for you. I studied extensively because I know that

00:50:49.079 --> 00:50:56.199
in the day and age in which we live, there's a battle that rages amongst Christendom on this

00:50:56.199 --> 00:51:03.079
subject of total abstinence or moderation. Is social drinking okay? And there is a ton of

00:51:03.079 --> 00:51:10.999
peer pressure that is put upon us. When I was a junior in high school, I had not even saved,

00:51:10.999 --> 00:51:16.519
but I was going to a church and I had not yet trusted Christ as my savior, but we were going

00:51:16.519 --> 00:51:20.119
to the church faithfully and I was trying to get some friends to go to church with me. And

00:51:20.279 --> 00:51:25.879
we were after a baseball game one evening and I was not at a party, none of that kind of stuff,

00:51:25.879 --> 00:51:29.559
but a friend, I said, I was thirsty. He said, here's a Coke, you can have it.

00:51:30.519 --> 00:51:36.439
And he had mixed that Coke with strong drink. And I just got it to here and I could smell it.

00:51:38.519 --> 00:51:41.079
You know what that person was trying to do? They were trying to deceive me

00:51:42.439 --> 00:51:47.159
to take that first drink. See, the world tells us we're missing out on something.

00:51:47.159 --> 00:51:54.119
You're missing out. I don't think so. That's right. Because with all of the marketing and

00:51:54.119 --> 00:51:58.439
all of the glamour and all of what the industry wants to tell you, you know what they forget to

00:51:58.439 --> 00:52:09.720
tell you? The fact that 40% of Americans have grown up in a home with an alcoholic, the abuse,

00:52:10.119 --> 00:52:16.279
the neglect. They fail to tell you about the people that have lost their lives because

00:52:16.279 --> 00:52:23.399
somebody gets behind a wheel of a vehicle after they're impaired. You see it on the news. You

00:52:23.399 --> 00:52:29.399
see it all around us. And this evening, we look at it, we say, listen, I'm not missing out on

00:52:29.399 --> 00:52:35.239
anything. They didn't know it. They didn't know what was going on. They didn't know what was

00:52:35.239 --> 00:52:41.000
going on. I'm not missing out on anything. They didn't know it. The Wheelocks this afternoon were

00:52:41.000 --> 00:52:44.119
having lunch. They made a statement. And I said, that's kind of funny because I'm going to be

00:52:44.119 --> 00:52:50.519
speaking on that subject this evening. Heather grabbed the menu and she said, look at the prices.

00:52:51.959 --> 00:52:55.399
Even if I wasn't a Christian, I wouldn't want to spend that kind of money on alcohol.

00:52:56.360 --> 00:53:00.279
That was kind of funny. It's not about money. It's not about health or science,

00:53:00.279 --> 00:53:03.879
about what the Bible says. And so this evening, I hope it was a help for you. Let's pray together.

00:53:03.879 --> 00:53:07.639
Father, we love you. We thank you for the opportunity to be in your house.

00:53:08.440 --> 00:53:11.720
We thank you for your word and for the truth that is contained therein.

00:53:13.080 --> 00:53:15.080
And God, I pray that your Holy Spirit would take

